%U A397869 4,0,5,6,5,4,1,1,7,2,0,3,2,8,4,3,6,2,0,3,9,4
%N A397869 Decimal expansion of the inradius of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397869 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397869 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397869/b397869.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397869 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397869 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397869 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397869 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_06">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 6</a>.
%F A397869 Equals sin(Pi/7)*sqrt((3 - 2*cos(Pi/7))*(4 - sec(Pi/14)^2))/(4*(4 + sin(3*Pi/14) - 5*cos(Pi/7))).
%F A397869 Equals the largest real root of 832*x^6 - 2528*x^4 + 212*x^2 + 1.
%e A397869 1.7181405195737569473896942645287248090977873150315...
%t A397869 First[RealDigits[Root[832*#^6 - 2528*#^4 + 212*#^2 + 1 &, 4], 10, 100]]
%t A397869 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397869 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 7}, "Inradius"], 10, 100]]
%Y A397869 Cf. A397867 (volume), A397868 (surface area), A397870 (midradius), A397871 (height).
%Y A397869 Cf. A397872 (long edge).
%Y A397869 Cf. A397873 (small face angle), A397874 (large face angle), A397875 (dihedral angle).
